Minder
======
1. Configure the log directory so that it can be written to by the web server

WHM
===
1. Modify your Apache config file to include the following. Note: The alias for /icons/ has been moved under /icons/whm/

<Directory "/var/www/minder">
    Options Indexes FollowSymLinks

    AllowOverride All

    Order allow,deny
    Allow from 192.168.61
    Satisfy Any
    AuthType Basic
    AuthName "Restricted Area"
    AuthUserFile /var/www/passwd
    AuthGroupFile /var/www/group
    Require valid-user
</Directory>
Alias /minder/ "/var/www/minder/www/"
Alias /whm/ "/var/www/minder/whm/html/"
Alias /icons/whm/ "/var/www/minder/whm/icons/"
Alias /icons/ "/var/www/icons/"

<Location />
    AuthType Basic
    AuthName "Restricted Area"
    AuthUserFile /var/www/passwd
    AuthGroupFile /var/www/group
    Require group bdcs
</Location>

<Location /whm>
    php_value include_path ".:/var/www/minder/whm/includes:/usr/local/lib/php"
    Require valid-user
</Location>

<Location /icons/whm>
    php_value include_path ".:/var/www/minder/whm/includes:/usr/local/lib/php"
    Require valid-user
</Location>


WarehouseMinder5
================
1. Copy WarehouseMinder5.war to /var/lib/tomcat5/webapps
2. Restart tomcat
3. Edit /var/lib/tomcat5/webapps/WarehouseMinder5/WEB-INF/web.xml and change the following settings
<context-param>
    <param-name>driverClass</param-name>
    <param-value>org.firebirdsql.jdbc.FBDriver</param-value>
</context-param>
<context-param>
    <param-name>jdbcURL</param-name>
    <param-value>jdbc:firebirdsql:192.168.61.164/3050:/data/asset.rf/wh.v39.gdb</param-value>
</context-param>
<context-param>
    <param-name>jdbcUser</param-name>
    <param-value>SYSDBA</param-value>
</context-param>
<context-param>
    <param-name>jdbcPassword</param-name>
    <param-value>masterkey</param-value>
</context-param>
4. Restart tomcat
